# Everything
- Decide if to embed root CA into crates
- Verify certificate revocation lists
- Measurement verification using constants in crates

# TDX
// Step 1: Verify TCB Info signature
// Step 2: Verify QE Identity signature
// Step 3: Verify PCK certificate chain
// Step 4: Verify QE Report signature
// Step 5: Verify QE Report content (hash check)
// Step 6: Verify QE Report policy\
// Step 7: Verify ISV Report signature
// Step 8: Match Platform TCB
// Step 9 & 10: QE TCB matching is done in verify_qe_identity_policy, merge statuses
// Validate report attributes (debug mode check, etc.)

## Fetching collateral

- get pck chain
  - either embedded (cert type 5)
  - or fetchable through encrypted PPID (cert type 2 or 3)
- extract FMSPC from certificate chain
  - get intel extension from certificate using the SGX OID EXTENSION
  - extract fmspc from intel extension (has its own FMPSC OID)
    - must be length 6
  - also extracts ca=(platform/processor) from issuer for some reason
- fetch collateral using fmspc, ca
  - fetch pck_crl and pck_crl issuer chain     <-- CERTIFICATE REVOCATION LIST
  - fetch tcb_info and tcb_info_issuer_chain
  - fetch qe_identity, qe_identity_issuer_chain
  ---
  - fetch CA certificate revocation list
  -

## Everything verification

- Check root CA to certificate revocation list
- Parse certificate revocation lists
- SGX TEE must have version 3, TDX TEE quote must have version 4 or 5
- Assert attestation key type
---
- Verify TCB info signature
  - parse from json tcb_info from collateral
  - check validity window (date)
  - check certificate chain against ca, leaf against cc, signature against Leaf
- Verify QE identity
  - parse qe identity
  - check validity window
  - check certificate chain against ca, leaf against cc, signature against Leaf
- Verify PCK certificate chain
- Verify QE report
    - verify signature using PCK leaf
    - verify content (hash)
- Verify QE report policy
- Verify ISV report signature
- Match QE TCB report signature

## Checking certificate chains

Trust anchor CA (embedded into crate?)  --> <Certificate chain> --> <Leaf certificate> --> Signature of whatever we are trying to verify


# Vocabulary
FMSPC: Family, Model, Stepping, Platform Type, and Customized SKU
ISV: the enclave we are attesting
